criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Male or female, at least 18 years of age;

          -  After standard clinical work-up a benign appearing lower bowel lesion >2cm in
             diameter;

          -  Patient or authorised representative able to comprehend and sign the Informed Consent
             prior to enrolment in the study.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Aged <18 years of age;

          -  Pregnant or lactating females;

          -  Lower bowel lesions <2cm in diameter;

          -  Patients receiving regular systemic steroids;

          -  Patients who are immuno-compromised (either acquired or congenital);

          -  Patients with a known coagulopathy (either acquired or congenital);

          -  Patients on anti-platelet therapy at the time of the procedure, apart from low dose
             (75mg) aspirin alone;

          -  Concurrent participation in another experimental intervention or drug study;

          -  Unwilling or unable to provide informed consent.
